task.summary: Elemenate some unused files. Add DCM_RNN package. Capsulate each experiments into an individual folder to make sure that each can be excuted independently and is reproducable. Next step: modify population module so that connection matrices can be randomly drawn.
Add modules utilities and tests into DCM_RNN package. Add utilities.randomly_generate_A_matrix function

Add utilities.randomly_generate_C_matrix. Separate utilities.check_transition_matrix from utilities.randomly_generate_A_matrix, so that it can be reused in tobe function utilities.randomly_generate_sparse_A_matrix
Add Utilities.randomly_generate_sparse_A_matrix Add DCM_RNN.notes.py for summary necessary parameters

Add functions for generating hemodynamic parameters Add Utilities.get_stardard_hemodynamic_parameters Add Utilities.get_hemodynamic_parameter_prior_distributions Add Utilities.get_hemodynamic_parameter_prior_distributions_as_dataframe Add Utilities.get_standard_hemodynamic_parameters Add Utilities.randomly_generate_hemodynamic_parameters Add Utilities.check_hemodynamic_parameters Add Utilities.if_proper_hemodynamic_parameters
Add functions for neural state initialization Add Utilities.set_initial_neural_state_as_zeros Add Utilities.sample_initial_neural_state
Add functions for hemodynamic state initialization Add Utilities.set_initial_hemodynamic_state_as_inactivated Add Utilities.sample_initial_hemodynamic_state

Update Rename utilities.Utilities to utilities.InitializationToolbox. Modify utilities.InitializationToolbox.get_hemodynamic_parameter_prior_distributions. It now return a pd.dataframe. Rename InitializationToolbox.get_hemodynamic_parameter_prior_distributions_as_dataframe to InitializationToolbox.get_expanded_hemodynamic_parameter_prior_distributions and modify it according the above modification.

Rename and restructure Rename utilities.py to toolboxes.py. All toolboxes used by DCM_RNN package will be put in it. Rename utilities.Utilities to toolboxes.Initialization. Functions in this toolbox are used to do parameter initialization. Add parameter_unit.py and parameter_unit.ParameterUnit. ParameterUnit will work as an unit containing all needed parameters and related operations. It calls toolboxes.Initialization.

Package structure rearrangement Remove parameter_unit.py Move the functionalities of population.py into CBI.py. Remove population.py Use CBI.Project to maintain a study. CBI.Project.plan_a_experiment() to set up all experimental parameters, like n_node, n_stimuli, t_delta, and u CBI.Project.recruit_a_subject() to set up all parameters related to subjects, like ABC and hemodynamic parameters, following experimental settings. It returns a Scan_ready_sheet object, containing all information needed for a scan. CBI.Scanner contains functionalities of a scanner. CBI.Scanner.make_a_scan() takes in a Scan_ready_sheet object and make a scan accordingly. It returns a Scan_result, which contains the Scan_ready_sheet and u, x, h, and y readings. Scan_result is the object feeding into following analysis.

Package structure rearrangement Project -> Study -> Study.plan_a_experiment -> -> Study.recruit_a_subject -> Study.make_scan_ready_sheets - scan_ready_sheet -> -> Scanner.make_a_scan() - scan_result -> Study.make_reports - reports -> further analysis
Project: inherits from dict, containing the information common to all its studies. Its dictionary items are studies; its attributes are used to store common information. Project.create_a_study() # create a study with project info, if not enough, more info is needed
Study: inherits from Object Study.experiment_plan, dictionary Study.subjects, dictionary with subID Study.scan_ready_sheets, dictionary with all info needed for scanning Study.scan_results, dictionary, each key is subID, each value is a dictionary containing x, h, and y Srudy.reports, dictionary, each key is subID, each value is a dictionary containing all above info
Study.plan_a_experiment() Study.generate_stimuli() Study.recruit_a_subject() Study.make_scan_ready_sheets() # used to join information of plan_a_experiment and recruit_a_subject Study.make_reports() # used to join information of scan_ready_sheets and scan_results Study.show_experiment_plan()
Scanner: inherits from Object Scanner.make_a_scan(), takes in scan_ready_sheets

Update toolboxes.Initialization Put hard-coded parameters into class attributes so that they can be accessed and modified with easy. Unify random number generation with uniform distribution with low and high. All member functions are modified accordingly. randomly_generate_sparse_A_matrix has all functionalities of randomly_generate_A_matrix, so remove randomly_generate_A_matrix and rename randomly_generate_sparse_A_matrix as randomly_generate_A_matrix
